Wash and dry produce.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @white wine vinegar{3%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1%teaspoon}(for 2 servings). Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use all the vinegar and 2 tsp sugar.

Evenly spread half the @sourdough bread{4%slice} with @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, then evenly top with @smoked deli ham{8%ounce} and @gouda cheese{2%slice}. Top with remaining sourdough slices to form sandwiches.

Heat @butter{1/2%tablespoon} and a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Once butter has melted, add sandwiches, cheese sides down. Push sandwiches around pan until butter and oil has absorbed. Cover and cook until bread is golden brown on one side and cheese begins to melt, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add another @butter{1/2%tablespoon} and drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} to pan and flip sandwiches. Push sandwiches around pan until butter and oil has absorbed. Cover and cook until bread is golden brown on second side and cheese melts, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, work in batches or use a second pan, wiping out pan between batches and adding 1⁄2 TBSP butter and a drizzle of oil for each side.

Halve melts on a diagonal.

Divide melts and coleslaw between #plates{}. Serve.